title: Maniac Episode 1 Explained!
author: Think Story
comment: I'll be coming out with a Maniac Ending Explained video by the end of the month. Work has gotten busy so this series was put on the backburner, but stay tuned.
When Annie picks up the rubix cube and tosses it behind her, you can see Owen in the background picking it up and then solving it in the next scene under the table.
You missed an easter egg when Owen is talking to his dad on the street a car drives by playing “My Mind Playin Tricks on Me” by Geto Boys. This is a reference to Owen’s schizophrenia.
I think I'm too dumb for this show

I don't think it's set in the future at all. I really thing it's an alternative reality that has to do with the Cold war and how it ended differently.
I think the whole idea behind the statue of Extra liberty is the fact that the Soviets won the war and enforced all of these ideas into society. Similar to the man in the high castle the Japanese also either won or have a huge influence thus investing in the US.
description:
A new series explaining the theories, mysteries, and easter eggs in episode one of Netflix's "Maniac" starring Jonah Hill, Emma Stone, and Justin Theroux.
